Posts.Content: May 24, 2013 10:18PM JennaJMU wrote: Twinmama, I just wanted to let you know I'm thinking of you and praying for the best. I understand where you are at, I was diagnosed in February at age 33 and with a 14 month old daughter. I cried every time I looked at her that first weekend after diagnosis. But then, if it is cancer, you get a plan in place. You have surgery, chemo, rads, hormone therapy, whatever you need to do to kick its ass to the curb so you never see it again. It's likely a year worth of hell, but it will be worth it. I'm right in the middle of chemo, and its doable. I wonder why I didn't find my tumor earlier when it was smaller but I will never wonder if I did enough treatment. You can and will do this!!!
